wo collective variables where the\ncommittor, the reactive current, and the transition rate are compared to those\ncomputed by the finite element method (FEM). Finally, tm-mmap is applied to\nalanine dipeptide in four collective variables where the use of finite elements\nis infeasible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 27 Aug 2022 03:22:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 2 Nov 2022 18:44:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-14"}
